    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Find the length of \(y = {@m@}x^{\frac{3}{2}}\) between \(x = {@a@}\) and \(x = {@b@}\). Give your answer in <b>exact</b> form.</p>
<p>The length is [[input:ans1]]</p>
<p>[[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p> Given \( y = {@y@} \) then \( \dfrac{dy}{dx} = {@dy@}.\)
<p>Using the formula \[\text{length of curve}=\int_a^b \sqrt{1+\left(\frac{\mathrm{d}y}{\mathrm{d}x}\right)^2} \ \mathrm{d}x,\] the length of the line is calculated to be: \[\ell = \int_{{@a@}}^{{@b@}} \sqrt{1+{@dy^2@}} \ \mathrm{d}x = \left[ {@I@} \right]_{{@a@}}^{{@b@}}={@ta1@}.\]</p>
For this integral you can use the substitution \( u= 1+{@dy^2@}.\)]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
